      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Melt, mix, and shape",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 190°C (170°C fan). Melt {{unsalted-butter}}, {{golden-syrup}}, and {{black-treacle}} together in a small saucepan over low heat, stirring until smooth. Remove from the heat. Combine {{plain-flour}}, {{caster-sugar}}, {{ginger-ground}}, {{bicarbonate-of-soda}}, and {{salt-table}} in a bowl. Pour in the melted mixture and stir to a stiff dough. Roll into walnut-sized balls (about 15 g each) and place on lined baking trays, spacing them at least 4 cm apart. They spread significantly.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake for 12 to 14 minutes until spread flat and darkened to a deep amber. They will crackle across the surface. Leave on the tray for 5 minutes before moving to a wire rack; they break easily while hot. They should be fully rigid within 30 minutes of cooling. Store in an airtight tin.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
